  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nAs of Quarkus 2.7.2 there can be classloading issues when running (field-stlye) ArchUnit tests and there is no way to exclude those, because the existing filters don't cover [`com.tngtech.archunit.junit.FieldSource`](https://github.com/TNG/ArchUnit/blob/v0.23.0/archunit-junit/junit5/engine-api/src/main/java/com/tngtech/archunit/junit/FieldSource.java) yet. See also: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/23358#discussion_r813325181\r\n\r\nOther auto-discovered engines might cause issues as well, so it would come in handy to exclude a certain engine via config.\r\n\r\nPS: My workaround for ArchUnit is the following (in a `qtest` Maven profile):\r\n```xml\r\n                <dependency>\r\n                    <groupId>com.tngtech.archunit</groupId>\r\n                    <artifactId>archunit-junit5</artifactId>\r\n                    <version>${archunit.version}</version>\r\n                    <scope>test</scope>\r\n                    <exclusions>\r\n                        <exclusion>\r\n                            <groupId>com.tngtech.archunit</groupId>\r\n                            <artifactId>archunit-junit5-engine</artifactId>\r\n                        </exclusion>\r\n                    </exclusions>\r\n                </dependency>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nThere is already `org.junit.platform.launcher.EngineFilter`, so the change looks easy.",
